The paper proposes a novel approach to extract and understand deep learning design flow diagrams and tables available in research papers and convert them to an abstract computational graph. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed approach is specifically targeted towards deep learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which is a subfield of computational neuroscience (cs.NE).
